news.title: Uttar Pradesh: 24 months or 46? Zero-period relief for developers isn't a blanket one
news.para: The zero-period relief, for one, will not be a blanket one when dues of realtors are recalculated. The Kant committee had suggested two zero periods, one for Covid (March 2020 to March 2022) and the other for construction curbs because of NGT orders (August 2013 to June 2015).

news.title: About 134 extra flats built without nod, HC wants probe by Ghaziabad development body
news.para: Officials said the developer of Express Garden in Vaibhav Khand had carved out 536 flats against the 402 units for which it had taken approval from GDA.

news.title: SBI Life Insurance told to pay up Rs 30 lakh outstanding house loan
news.para: The forum said not conducting medical tests before issuance of policy and then repudiating the claim in the guise of an investigation was unfair trade practice.

news.title: Over one lakh complaints by homebuyers resolved by RERA of various states
news.para: Out of this, 38% cases (approximately 44,602 complaints) were resolved in Uttar Pradesh alone, followed by Haryana with 20,604 cases (18%) and Maharashtra with 15,423 cases (13%).

news.title: Home prices in Germany tumble amid property rout
news.para: It was the fourth consecutive quarter of declines and the biggest since Germany's statistics office began keeping records in the year 2000, underscoring the nation's biggest property crisis in decades.

news.title: Awfis Space Solutions files DRHP with Sebi
news.para: Awfis' initial public offering comprises a fresh issue of up to Rs 160 crore and an offer for sale of equity shares of up to 10,023,172 equity shares.

news.title: Kochi: Infopark to open flexible workspaces
news.para: KMRL MD Loknath Behera and Infopark CEO Susanth Kurunthil signed the MoU to set up flexi workspaces on 39,880 sq ft of built-up space across six floors of the Metro station.

news.title: Nagpur metro phase II to be ready by 2027, Housing minster tells Parliament
news.para: The Centre considers funding the Metro project in any state depending upon feasibility of the proposal and availability of the resources.

news.title: Pune civic body may tax PG facilities, hostels at commercial rates
news.para: The Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) administration would table a proposal before the civic standing committee and bring about the changes from the next financial year.

news.title: Greater Noida’s Sky Garden project to be revived under the new policy of UP government
news.para: The Greater Noida authority has issued an order in this regard, allowing Hawelia Group, a real estate developer, to take control of a 22-acre partially completed undertaking known as Shree Radha Sky Garden in Greater Noida.

news.title: Assam government approves draft Guwahati central area local area plan
news.para: The proposed LAP aims to make provisions for redevelopment and upgrade infrastructure facilities, open spaces, ensure better connectivity to each plot and optimum utilisation of urban land in Guwahati.

news.title: Odisha RERA tells builders to upload sale agreement
news.para: In a letter to builders, ORERA said the proforma of allotment letters, agreement of sale and conveyance deed proposed to be signed with allottees must be uploaded for the information of homebuyers.

news.title: Karnataka government slashes beneficiary share for housing scheme
news.para: Currently, beneficiaries contribute Rs 4.5 lakh, while the state and Centre contribute Rs 1.5 lakh each. The cost of a house under the scheme is Rs 7.5 lakh.

news.title: Tamil Nadu housing board fixes prices of HIG flats
news.para: ​The flats constructed under the self-finance scheme will be sold to the general public at `75 lakh to `78 lakh per unit. Further, the TNHB has proposed to develop separate high-rise towers in the same location for the middle-income group (MIG) and low-income group (LIG) .

news.title: Private equity inflow in real estate declines 44% to USD 3 billion so far this year: Knight Frank
news.para: Knight Frank India released its data showing that the Indian real estate market received USD 3,024 million in PE investments from 23 deals between January 1 and December 12 this year, as against USD 5,357 million recorded in 2022.

news.title: Violations many, flat extensions cut to 0.75m in Uttar Pradesh
news.para: The limit, which has been ambiguous till now, allowed people to build ramps that encroach upon roads. The slope gradient of the ramp should be in the 1:8 ratio.

news.title: MCD serves eviction notices to flat owners in all towers of Signature View Apartments
news.para: RWA secretary of Signature View Apartments, Gaurav Pandey, said that the notices were placed in four blocks by the MCD staff and it applied to all the apartments in 12 towers.

news.title: NCLT admits insolvency plea against Ansal Properties' promoter
news.para: NCLT's has directed the appointment of Roshan Lal Jain as the resolution professional to verify the claims made by Indian Bank against Ansal. Indian Bank has claimed that Ansal has defaulted on dues of ₹76 crore for which payment was personally guaranteed by him.

news.title: Brigade Group lease out 54,000 sq ft office space to Sidvin Core-Tech India
news.para: Brigade Deccan Heights spans 2.2 acres with a 4.3 lakh sq ft development area.

news.title: MakeMyTrip's CEO, Genpact's CHRO buys apartment in Gurugram for around Rs 33 crore each
news.para: All three Golf Links projects — the Aralias, the Magnolias, and the Camellias — have witnessed significant price increases since last year as same sized apartment was sold at Rs 19 crore in October 2022.
